{"questionId":"22265","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℂ</mi></math>.&nbsp;The roots of this equation are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Im</mi><mfenced><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Im</mi><mfenced><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The roots <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> are represented by the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> respectively on an&nbsp;Argand diagram.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AC</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid attempt to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>or</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>2</mn></mstyle></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>valid attempt to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AC</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3</strong></em><em><strong>&nbsp;marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22265","referenceCode":"21N.1.AHL.TZ0.12c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find AC.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers – Cartesian form and Argand diag","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Complex roots of polynomials, conjugate roots, De Moivre’s, powers & roots of complex numbers"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}